    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-c065d8e7-7fff-ec0f-bdcd-865d8e6df40c\" dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-indent:13.5pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">Prerequisites </span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">tribe of bones, trained in Deception</span></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-indent:13.5pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">When you reach 0 hit points, you appear entirely dead. You also gain twice as many temporary hit points as your level that remain for 10 minutes. You may then either fall prone and appear dead as usual, or continue the battle with all the appearance of the undead. You may start moving at any time, but doing so ruins the appearance of being properly dead. Once it activates, it will not activate again until you have been healed of all your damage. A creature attempting to notice you playing dead must Seek against your Deception DC.</span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>"
